{"pagelen": 100, "values": [{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/blacs/issues/17/comments/37602109.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/blacs/issues/17#comment-37602109"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/blacs/issues/17.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 17, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/blacs.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/blacs"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{50ed1eb9-8c1b-4afe-a8b8-8e0a33b39a05}ts=249915"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "BLACS", "full_name": "labscript_suite/blacs", "uuid": "{50ed1eb9-8c1b-4afe-a8b8-8e0a33b39a05}"}, "title": "Tab becomes unselected when moving"}, "content": {"raw": "I'm going to have a look at this now. The code for this is a complete mess because it was one of the first things I wrote while trying to learn Qt...I'll see if I can improve it.\n\nIt is worth noting that the behaviour may be different between windows and linux/OSX due to the behaviour of [`QDrag.exec()`](http://doc.qt.io/qt-4.8/qdrag.html#exec) which blocks on windows and doesn't on linux/OSX!", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I'm going to have a look at this now. The code for this is a complete mess because it was one of the first things I wrote while trying to learn Qt...I'll see if I can improve it.</p>\n<p>It is worth noting that the behaviour may be different between windows and linux/OSX due to the behaviour of <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"http://doc.qt.io/qt-4.8/qdrag.html#exec\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code>QDrag.exec()</code></a> which blocks on windows and doesn't on linux/OSX!</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-06-15T04:36:53.820196+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Philip Starkey", "uuid": "{48af65db-e5fc-459c-a7eb-52eb1f9a5690}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B48af65db-e5fc-459c-a7eb-52eb1f9a5690%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B48af65db-e5fc-459c-a7eb-52eb1f9a5690%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/dc318537facc47ebe1ae98a7aabacecfd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsPS-0.png"}}, "nickname": "pstarkey", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:52a111e4-40da-4441-9143-417f95f2db97"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 37602109}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/blacs/issues/17/comments/37602185.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/blacs/issues/17#comment-37602185"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/blacs/issues/17.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 17, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/blacs.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/blacs"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{50ed1eb9-8c1b-4afe-a8b8-8e0a33b39a05}ts=249915"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "BLACS", "full_name": "labscript_suite/blacs", "uuid": "{50ed1eb9-8c1b-4afe-a8b8-8e0a33b39a05}"}, "title": "Tab becomes unselected when moving"}, "content": {"raw": "I'm still not exactly sure what conditions are required to get this to happen, but it seems to be speed related. It could be shaking fast, and moving the mouse outside of the tab area briefly, or just the fast movement. Either way, this isn't a huge priority, as it doesn't break anything, it's just a little odd. I suppose it's worth investigating if it helps to clean up the code a bit!", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I'm still not exactly sure what conditions are required to get this to happen, but it seems to be speed related. It could be shaking fast, and moving the mouse outside of the tab area briefly, or just the fast movement. Either way, this isn't a huge priority, as it doesn't break anything, it's just a little odd. I suppose it's worth investigating if it helps to clean up the code a bit!</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-06-15T04:44:01.328690+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Shaun Johnstone", "uuid": "{652df738-313d-472c-b7b5-a3f8f98a3322}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B652df738-313d-472c-b7b5-a3f8f98a3322%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B652df738-313d-472c-b7b5-a3f8f98a3322%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/38984f1761fc67ce892911496abee619d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSJ-3.png"}}, "nickname": "shjohnst", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:1b9a15fb-8e4f-407e-b7b9-567c5e1fa1b4"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 37602185}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/blacs/issues/17/comments/37602213.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/blacs/issues/17#comment-37602213"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/blacs/issues/17.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 17, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/blacs.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/blacs"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{50ed1eb9-8c1b-4afe-a8b8-8e0a33b39a05}ts=249915"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "BLACS", "full_name": "labscript_suite/blacs", "uuid": "{50ed1eb9-8c1b-4afe-a8b8-8e0a33b39a05}"}, "title": "Tab becomes unselected when moving"}, "content": {"raw": "I think I've reproduced it.\n\nStart with a tab to the right as being active (note, I think the tab bar needs to not be full, but perhaps not)\nNow click and drag the left most tab towards the right and keep moving your mouse until you go beyond the right most tab and the mouse shows the \"drop\" icon. \nThen when you release, no tab is highlighted!\n\nI've also managed to hard-crash python a few times by rearranging things too fast which is more of a concern...", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I think I've reproduced it.</p>\n<p>Start with a tab to the right as being active (note, I think the tab bar needs to not be full, but perhaps not)\nNow click and drag the left most tab towards the right and keep moving your mouse until you go beyond the right most tab and the mouse shows the \"drop\" icon. \nThen when you release, no tab is highlighted!</p>\n<p>I've also managed to hard-crash python a few times by rearranging things too fast which is more of a concern...</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-06-15T04:46:49.773866+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Philip Starkey", "uuid": "{48af65db-e5fc-459c-a7eb-52eb1f9a5690}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B48af65db-e5fc-459c-a7eb-52eb1f9a5690%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B48af65db-e5fc-459c-a7eb-52eb1f9a5690%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/dc318537facc47ebe1ae98a7aabacecfd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsPS-0.png"}}, "nickname": "pstarkey", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:52a111e4-40da-4441-9143-417f95f2db97"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 37602213}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/blacs/issues/17/comments/38919895.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/blacs/issues/17#comment-38919895"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/blacs/issues/17.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 17, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/blacs.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/blacs"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{50ed1eb9-8c1b-4afe-a8b8-8e0a33b39a05}ts=249915"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "BLACS", "full_name": "labscript_suite/blacs", "uuid": "{50ed1eb9-8c1b-4afe-a8b8-8e0a33b39a05}"}, "title": "Tab becomes unselected when moving"}, "content": {"raw": "I think these issues are resolved by @cbillington 's [new drag drop tab](#!/labscript_suite/labscript_utils/pull-requests/21/dragdroptab/diff). Maybe have a look at that.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I think these issues are resolved by @cbillington 's <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/labscript_suite/labscript_utils/pull-requests/21/dragdroptab/diff\" rel=\"nofollow\">new drag drop tab</a>. Maybe have a look at that.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-08-06T11:50:52.791422+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Jan Werkmann", "uuid": "{44c4905c-2b90-4045-a5f1-652b8e228626}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B44c4905c-2b90-4045-a5f1-652b8e228626%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B44c4905c-2b90-4045-a5f1-652b8e228626%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:a70cc9cf-684e-4849-a61a-9ade4d7218b5/07e5095a-4741-4dc0-a462-9c7d455f961d/128"}}, "nickname": "PhyNerd", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:a70cc9cf-684e-4849-a61a-9ade4d7218b5"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 38919895}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/blacs/issues/17/comments/47145568.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/blacs/issues/17#comment-47145568"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/blacs/issues/17.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 17, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/labscript_suite/blacs.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/labscript_suite/blacs"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{50ed1eb9-8c1b-4afe-a8b8-8e0a33b39a05}ts=249915"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "BLACS", "full_name": "labscript_suite/blacs", "uuid": "{50ed1eb9-8c1b-4afe-a8b8-8e0a33b39a05}"}, "title": "Tab becomes unselected when moving"}, "content": {"raw": "Resolved by pull request #21", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Resolved by <a href=\"#!/labscript_suite/blacs/pull-requests/21/fixed-a-bug-when-adding-files\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">pull request #21</a></p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-08-07T06:16:31.922536+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "